sentences.english: Coriolis acceleration is a nodus in general mechanics.
sentences.chinese: 科里奥利加速度在普通物理力学中是一难点。

sentences.english: You can manifest psionic powers more powerful than the normal limits of manifestation.
sentences.chinese: 你可以展现比普通极限更强的灵能。

sentences.english: She says my roommate decorates her bed so nice, and mind was just normal.
sentences.chinese: 她说我室友的床单那么美，而我得那么的普通。

sentences.english: "This case is no different than any other case, " Lott said yesterday.
sentences.chinese: “这只是一件普通的案子而已，”洛特昨天表示。

sentences.english: Some laminates are available in plain colors, too.
sentences.chinese: 一些层板可在普通的颜色，太。

sentences.english: Judge-made law is called common law.
sentences.chinese: 法官造法就被称为普通法。

sentences.english: It is a dense material – different from surrounding soil – and therefore discernible.
sentences.chinese: 和普通的泥块不同，泥砖是一种十分紧实的材料。

sentences.english: Some arise from common law. Others are statutory.
sentences.chinese: 它们有些源起于普通法，其他则是属于成文法。

sentences.english: Are there any requirements of exterior wall thermal insulation practice?Use common rockwool board.
sentences.chinese: 外墙保温做法有什么要求？采用普通岩棉板。

sentences.english: It is ordinary arithmetic that the stronger will win, so why fight?
sentences.chinese: 强者会胜是一种很普通的算术，那为什么争斗？

sentences.english: This allegory program will show a direct tentacles extending toward China ordinary family sedan.
sentences.chinese: 这喻示着福特公司将触角直接伸向中国普通家庭轿车。

sentences.english: What kind of hotel would you like, five-star or something simpler?
sentences.chinese: 您愿意要什么样的酒店，五星级的还是普通些的？

sentences.english: They may look like an ordinary pair of spectacles, but these glasses are at the forefront of a revolution in eyewear.
sentences.chinese: 它们看起来像普通的眼镜，但是是眼镜改革的最前沿。

sentences.english: These components provide general utility functions.
sentences.chinese: 这些组件提供普通的实用功能。

sentences.english: Boring white paper? Too commonplace. Let's find something a little more eyecatching.
sentences.chinese: 乏味的白色的纸？太普通了，得找个稍微抢眼的。
